
*** Working with user permission ***

1.chmod  -To change the access permissions of files and directories.
1.1 chmod  -To gives the write and excecute permission to group members.
1.2 chmod u=rwx,o-wx filname  -This gives the read,write,excecute permission to owners and removes write and excecute ownership from other members


2.chown  -To change the owner of file and directories.
2.1 chown username filename  -Change the owner of the specified file.
2.2 chownnusename:groupname filename  -Change the owner and group ownership of the specifed file.


3.chgrp  -To change the group ownership of file and directories.
3.1 chgrp groupname filename  -Change the group ownership of the specified file.


